==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pharmacognosis
<hw>Phar`ma*cog*no"sis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>fa`rmakon</grk> a drug + <grk>gnw^sis</grk> a knowing.]</ety>
<def>That branch of pharmacology which treats of unprepared medicines or
simples; -- usually called <altname>pharmacognosy</altname>, and also
<altname>pharmacography</altname>, and
<altname>pharmacomathy</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pharmacognosy</ent>⟦br⟧
